The five colours blind us.
The five notes deafen us.
The five tastes deaden us.
Pursuing and catching
Disturb the mind.
Wanting scarce things
Delays our progress.
So the wise areï¼š
For the stomach
And not the eye.
Taking the one, they leave the other.
